in the end the only constant is change

This is also super bullish for crypto because 
1. Easier to distribute coin - transparency
2. Machines can use crypto

But with the current system dynamic all these people will have to suffer, one way or the other

so UBI is inevitable

Or whatever is called

The #1 job in the world is driving

Self driving soon to be fully automated (really close thanks to Tesla) - which is great because it relieves humanity from the pain of driving and saves so many lives it also increases the avg quality of life

Automation is also sth that will indirectly nudge towards this direction too

The working week for humans has been declining steadily since the 1900s
Was 100 hrs  and not good unhealthy conditions
Today 40 hrs a week with part time being the preferred option - comfortable living

Hot take(?)
Governments should pay tax to their people

Government owns all the non private land, so they need to use that land to generate revenue to

1. Maximize living quality
2. Pay tax to the people

We the people vote for the competitive managers that pay better
